quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  16,90,"Allah enjoins justice, kindness, and giving relatives [their dues], and He forbids shameful acts, evil deeds and oppression. He exhorts you, so that you may take heed"
  16,91,"Fulfill the covenant of Allah when you pledge, and do not break oaths after confirming them, having made Allah your witness, for Allah knows all that you do"
  16,92,"Do not be like the woman who unravels her yarn after spinning it firmly, by taking your oaths as a means of deceit between yourselves so that one party might gain advantage over the other. Allah only puts you to test thereby, and on the Day of Resurrection He will surely make clear to you all that over which you used to differ"
  16,93,"If Allah had willed, He would have made all of you a single community [of believers], but He causes to stray whom He wills and guides whom He wills, and you will surely be questioned about what you used to do"
  16,94,"Do not take your oaths as a means of deceit between yourselves, lest some feet will slip after they have been firm, and you will taste the evil consequences of preventing people from the way of Allah, and for you there will be a great punishment"
  16,95,"Do not trade the covenant of Allah for a small price. Indeed, what is with Allah is best for you, if only you knew"
  16,96,"Whatever you have will come to an end, but whatever Allah has will last forever. And We will surely grant those who remain steadfast their reward according to the best of their deeds"
  16,97,"Whoever does righteous deeds, male or female, while being a believer, We will surely grant him a good life, and We will surely reward them according to the best of their deeds"
  16,98,"When you recite the Qur’an, seek refuge with Allah from the accursed Satan"
  16,99,"Indeed, he has no power over those who believe and put their trust in their Lord"
  16,100,"He only has power over those who take him as their patron, and under his influence, associate partners with Allah"
  16,101,"When We replace one verse with another – and Allah knows best what He sends down – they say, “You are just making it up.” In fact, most of them have no knowledge"
  16,102,"Say, “This has been brought down by the Holy Spirit from your Lord with the truth, to strengthen those who believe, and as guidance and glad tidings to the Muslims.”"
  16,103,"We surely know that they say, “It is only a human being who teaches him.” But the language they refer to is foreign, whereas this is eloquent Arabic language"
  16,104,"Those who do not believe in the verses of Allah, Allah will not guide them, and for them there will be a painful punishment"
  16,105,No one fabricates lies except those who do not believe in the verses of Allah; it is they who are the liars
  16,106,"Whoever disbelieves in Allah after having believed – except one who is compelled while his heart is firm in faith – but those who embrace disbelief willingly, upon them will be the wrath of Allah, and for them there will be a great punishment"
  16,107,"That is because they prefer the life of this world to the Hereafter, and Allah does not guide the disbelieving people"
  16,108,"These are the ones whose hearts, hearing and sight are sealed up by Allah; it is they who are the heedless"
  16,109,No doubt that it is they who will be the greatest losers in the Hereafter
  16,110,"As for those who emigrated after being persecuted, then strove [for the cause of Allah], and were patient – indeed, your Lord is after that All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"